  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      patients are given bupivacain intermittent locally on the donor site after brest
      reconstruction with diep flap. The hypothesis was that this approach will reduce the need for
      rescue analgetic medication and pain perception within the three first days
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
